for_developers/README.md
     1тЖТ# For developers
     3тЖТWhile `mdbook` is mainly used as a command line tool, you can also import the
     4тЖТunderlying libraries directly and use those to manage a book. It also has a fairly
     5тЖТflexible plugin mechanism, allowing you to create your own custom tooling and
     6тЖТconsumers (often referred to as *backends*) if you need to do some analysis of
     7тЖТthe book or render it in a different format.
     8тЖТ
     9тЖТThe *For Developers* chapters are here to show you the more advanced usage of
    10тЖТ`mdbook`.
    11тЖТ
    12тЖТThe two main ways a developer can hook into the book's build process is via,
    13тЖТ
    14тЖТ- [Preprocessors](preprocessors.md)
    15тЖТ- [Alternative Backends](backends.md)
    16тЖТ
    17тЖТ## The build process
    19тЖТThe process of rendering a book project goes through several steps.
    20тЖТ
    21тЖТ1. Load the book
      тЖТтАж
    30тЖТ## Using `mdbook` as a library
    32тЖТThe `mdbook` binary is just a wrapper around the underlying mdBook crates,
    33тЖТexposing their functionality as a command-line program. If you want to
    34тЖТprogrammatically drive mdBook, you can use the [`mdbook-driver`] crate.
      тЖТтАж
